The man was shot in Date Palm Street in Bonteheuwel. Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said they were investigating. “A case of murder has been opened for investigation following a shooting incident that occurred on (Sunday night) in Date Palm Street, Bonteheuwel. According to information, police attended to the shooting incident. "(Police) found the body of a man with gunshot wounds to his body in the street.” Ward councillor Angus McKenzie said he suspected the shooting to be gang-related. “We appreciate the help of the police and the community for sharing information. It shows the system is working and if gangsters are wiping out themselves, I couldn’t care less. "However, if innocent people were dying, I would have a different approach,” McKenzie said. Cape Times